spanGrp.span: ‘The road comes from Buenos Aires to where we live.
(_) Ñala bötö-gẽu ñala ñala bötö-gẽu Buenos_Aires ji ji sa sẽr-gẽ wa
The place where we live is called Ujarraz.
Sa sẽr-gẽ wa kã' kie rö Ujarras
The road is not/by this road we get to Salitre.
ñala (_) ñala wa sa dagöũ Salitre
From there, the road comes straight
ñala jugö ska jera ñala bötöu ñawösiga
and gets to a place called Cucarachas, Roaches.
Dagou mãjuir kã' kie-ite (_) kã' kie kã' kie-nã Kukarachas Sotkö ska
We get then to the Chölöli [River] side
Se bötöu dajũ dia Chölöli kö ska
and come to the Ceibo River Bridge.
Se bötöu dagoũ Bikës puente ska
And going upwards we immediately get right to the middle of Ujarraz.
(_) Se bötöu juigweta ye dögaũ Ujarras puro sha sha ska plaja
